== Installing Utilmm ==

Note for Debian users: a quick install guide is included at the
bottom of this file

=== Getting the sources

  darcs get --set-scripts-executable http://www.laas.fr/~sjoyeux/darcs/utilmm

=== Dependencies and installation instructions
To build the library, you need the following:
 * the boost libraries, including the following:
    boost/thread
    boost/regex
    boost/filesystem
    boost/graph

 * libtool, autoconf and automake

When all these dependencies are installed, run
  ./autogen.sh
  ./configure
  make

And, as root,
  make install

=== Quick Debian installation guide
Run as root
  apt-get install build-essential libtool libboost-dev libboost-filesystem-dev libboost-thread-dev libboost-regex-dev libboost-graph-dev autoconf automake

Run as a normal user
  ./autogen.sh
  ./configure
  make

Run as root
  make install

